title: Gun Scare Triggers Multiple Sydney Schools To Lockdown | 10 News
description: A fake gun has caused a very real panic in Sydney’s northwest, with half a dozen schools forced into lockdown. The concern was raised when a member of the public saw a man on the street with a weapon that, it turns out, was a toy plucked from a pile of junk that had been left on the footpath for council clean-up. title: Mother Calls For Tougher Domestic Violence Sentencing After Daughter’s Murder | 10 News+
description: Tabitha Acret has made it her mission to fight against domestic violence since the murder of her daughter, Mackenzie Anderson. She was 21 years old when her former partner, Tyrone Thompson, stabbed her 78 times inside her Newcastle unit in front of a toddler. Thompson was sentenced to 22 years and 6 months in jail, with a non-parole period of 15 and a half years. Since the ruling, Mackenzie’s mother has worked tirelessly to change the system and that reform has now arrived. title: Ukrainian, US & European Officials 'Make Substantial Progress' In Peace Deal Talks | 10 News+
description: US Secretary of State Marco Rubio says "substantial progress" was made in Geneva after top Ukrainian, US and European officials met to discuss Donald Trump's 28-point peace plan for Ukraine. It comes after Kyiv and its allies expressed concern over what they saw as major concessions to Russia, and pressed for changes. Ukrainian forces fighting on the frontline are outrightly rejecting the idea of giving up land they currently control to their enemy.
